QUESTIONS TO BE ANSWERED¶

  • add image about the questions to be answered

For this project I want to explore if there is a way to build a recommendation system for a given consumer profile. The recommendation system will output a list of ten songs that it believes the user will enjoy. These songs will be based on a variety of ML models and techniques. Firstly, I will utilize a dataset of over 20k songs with multiple genre labels to merge labels onto a dataset of 1.2 million songs. Based on track similarity, I will build a KNN model that output the five most common sub-genres based on the song's N nearest neighbors. From these genre-typing, I will link different consumer profiles and their reported genre of choice with possible playlists of interest.

  • Potential Challenges:
    • Currently, I do not believe that I have sufficeint consumer data to link favorite genre types between the models.
    • Additionally, the length and detail between the genre types in two of my datasets is not coherent. I will need to find a way to bridge the gap between the detail assigned to each genre.

COLLABORATION PLAN¶

  • I will be working by myself for this project. My current goals are to spend 1-2 hours in non-deadline weeks working towards the completion of this project. Additionally, I want to regularly attend office hours to see if there are areas of my code that I can optimize or models that would more effeciently achieve my goals.

WHAT DATA WILL I USE?¶

  • Redo data set photos

All of the data that I downloaded was from Kaggle and there was no importing or cleaning issues. For the most part, all dataframes also had very little nan values.

The dataset below contains information on a unique track in Spotify. There are over 1.2 million tracks represented. For every track a series of features are recorded. These features can range from tempo to the amount of accosticness. This dataset could be used to predict any one of the feature variables based on the other reported feature variables. Additionally, depending on computing power, you could build a classification model that clusters songs based on their features. Thus creating your own genres based on the most similar songs

## combining mutlitple columns into two similarity columns

X_pca = pca.fit_transform(subset)
# creting a dataframe and merging the main genre type
X_pca = pd.DataFrame(X_pca, columns=["Component One", "Component Two"])
X_pca = pd.merge(merge[['main_cat']], X_pca, left_index = True, right_index = True)

Models and Where I'm Going:¶

  • From here I want to first build a model that will train on song features and output a predicted genre. I will train on the multi_genre dataframe and predict on the 1.2M song dataframe. I will use overlap between these two dataframes as validation data.
  • The second model that I will build is to utilize the genres associated with each of the playlists and assign songs from the 1.2 M dataframe into the given playlists. I will utilize a KNN model based on the newly assigned genres as well as song features.
  • Lastly, I want to attempt to use the consumer data profiles and their reported song preferences to assign a playlist to them, thus completeing the recommendation engine.
